args: All right, that's all the shopping.\nWhat say we go have some fun, Hawk?
Noisy environments are not my forte.
Aw, c'mon. Don't be like that.\nA bit of fun never hurt no one.
It's you, isn't it?! I never dreamed I'd run\ninto you here!
I've been looking for you for so long.\nWhere have you been?
...I'm sorry, but my name is Hawk.
You have mistaken me for someone else.
What's yer deal, Hawk? It ain't like ya\nto get this flustered.
Might I ask a favor, Ranzal?
Yeah. This is where that Silva guy yer\nlookin' for was laid to rest.
I found him lyin' on the ground a while\nback. Tried to do what I could, but he was\nreally weak and didn't last long.
Sorry. I only know his name, so I can't\neven join ya in reminiscin' about the guy.
Well, I feel like a total crumbum now,\nso thanks for that.
You at least gonna tell me the score?
...The story I'm about to tell is of a man\nwho is no longer in this world.
His name was Silva, and he had three very\ndear friends. The energetic Grayson, \nthe clever Marcos, and the kindly Villea.
Silva, Grayson, and Marcos were all in\nlove with Villea, so they made a promise\nbetween themselves.
They promised to all grow up and become\nfine men capable of making her happy.
Grayson grew up to become a knight,\nand Marcos a priest. But as for Silva...
Well, he became known as the Reaper.
But he had no regrets, even though the life\nof an assassin meant he could no longer\nsee her.
For he was sure that the other two\nwould make her happy in his place.
But one day, he received two\nassassination requests.
One was for Grayson.\nThe other was for Marcos.
Even though he was now the Reaper,\nSilva could not kill his childhood friends.
So he decided to tell them the truth.
He admitted that he was the Reaper\nand had been sent to kill them.
But that decision came back to haunt him.
The two requests had been sent by\nGrayson and Marcos themselves.
The two of them had become political\nrivals in their new positions and wanted\nto be rid of one another.
That was how they came to turn to a\nskilled assassin, completely unaware\nthat he was their old friend.
But once he found out the truth, it was too\nlate; they had already been killed.
Upon learning that Silva would not take\ntheir requests, they had both hired\nsomeone else.

Thus, Silva lost two of his friends at the
same time. Alone and ashamed,
he fled his homeland and left his
name behind forever.
All that stands before you is a single\npitiful hawk with nowhere to roost and\nrest his wings.
Damn, that's rough. So then that girl...
Was Villea, yes. I haven't seen her since\nwe were children; I can't believe she\nfigured me out.
Ya sure that's how you really want things\nto end?
I stole her happiness; the truth cannot\ngive that back.
Sometimes I still find myself regretting\nwhat I did.
If I had chosen to kill either Grayson or \nMarcos, the other would have lived.
Perhaps the survivor could have made her\nhappy. But now...
No matter how much time passes,\nI still don't know if my decision was right.
